## Part A — Terminal / Environment Setup

Run in **Anaconda Prompt** or terminal with conda on PATH.

```bash
# 1. Create a clean environment with Python 3.11
conda create -n bbb_env python=3.11 -y
conda activate bbb_env

# 2. Install NumPy as a pre-built binary (avoids compiler errors)
conda install -c conda-forge numpy=1.26.4 -y

# 3. Install PyTDC (now resolves against the pre-installed numpy)
pip install PyTDC

# 4. Verify the core install
python -c "import numpy; print(numpy.__version__)"
python -c "from tdc.single_pred import ADME; print('TDC OK')"

# 5. Install remaining pipeline dependencies
conda install -c conda-forge pandas scikit-learn rdkit -y
pip install PyTDC deepchem mordred
```

