## Part B — Jupyter Notebook: Dataset Loaders

> Each cell below corresponds to one of the six BBB dataset sources referenced in the pipeline run. Adjust file paths to match your local `BBB_predictor` directory structure.

### Cell 1 — Imports

```python
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import os

DATA_DIR = "data/raw"
os.makedirs(DATA_DIR, exist_ok=True)
```

### Cell 2 — B3DB

```python
# B3DB: https://github.com/theochem/B3DB
b3db_path = os.path.join(DATA_DIR, "B3DB_classification.tsv")
df_b3db = pd.read_csv(b3db_path, sep="\t")
print(f"B3DB: {df_b3db.shape[0]} compounds")
```

### Cell 3 — BBBP

```python
# BBBP: MoleculeNet Blood-Brain Barrier Penetration dataset
bbbp_url = "https://deepchemdata.s3-us-west-1.amazonaws.com/datasets/BBBP.csv"
df_bbbp = pd.read_csv(bbbp_url)
print(f"BBBP: {df_bbbp.shape[0]} compounds")
```

### Cell 4 — LightBBB

```python
# LightBBB: https://github.com/theocbc/LightBBB
try:
    lightbbb_url = "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/theocbc/LightBBB/main/dataset/BBB_dataset.csv"
    df_lightbbb = pd.read_csv(lightbbb_url)
    print(f"LightBBB: {df_lightbbb.shape[0]} compounds")
except Exception as e:
    print(f"LightBBB failed: {e}")
    # Fallback: load from local copy if previously downloaded
    df_lightbbb = pd.read_csv(os.path.join(DATA_DIR, "LightBBB_dataset.csv"))
    print(f"LightBBB (local fallback): {df_lightbbb.shape[0]} compounds")
```

### Cell 5 — PyTDC (BBB_Martins)

```python
from tdc.single_pred import ADME

tdc_data = ADME(name='BBB_Martins')
df_tdc = tdc_data.get_data()
print(f"TDC (BBB_Martins): {df_tdc.shape[0]} compounds")
```

### Cell 6 — DeePred-BBB

```python
# DeePred-BBB: dataset typically sourced from paper supplementary material
# (original hosted URL returned 404 — see Part D for recovery steps)
deepred_path = os.path.join(DATA_DIR, "DeePred_BBB_dataset.csv")
try:
    df_deepred = pd.read_csv(deepred_path)
    print(f"DeePred-BBB: {df_deepred.shape[0]} compounds")
except FileNotFoundError:
    print("DeePred-BBB: file not found locally — download from paper supplementary/Zenodo first")
```

### Cell 7 — ChEMBL (curated)

```python
# ChEMBL: curated subset (e.g. via chembl_webresource_client or pre-exported CSV)
chembl_path = os.path.join(DATA_DIR, "ChEMBL_BBB_curated.csv")
df_chembl = pd.read_csv(chembl_path)
print(f"ChEMBL curated: {df_chembl.shape[0]} compounds")
```

### Cell 8 — Summary Report

```python
sources = {
    "B3DB": df_b3db.shape[0],
    "BBBP": df_bbbp.shape[0],
    "LightBBB": df_lightbbb.shape[0] if 'df_lightbbb' in dir() else 0,
    "TDC (BBB_Martins)": df_tdc.shape[0] if 'df_tdc' in dir() else 0,
    "DeePred-BBB": df_deepred.shape[0] if 'df_deepred' in dir() else 0,
    "ChEMBL curated": df_chembl.shape[0],
}

for name, count in sources.items():
    status = "✓" if count > 0 else "✗"
    print(f"  {status} {name:<18}: {count:,} compounds")

print(f"\nTotal (pre-deduplication): {sum(sources.values()):,} compounds")
```

